---
alwaysApply: true
---

The app must support full localization (English + Arabic) from the beginning.

Rules:

1. No hardcoded text is allowed anywhere in UI.
2. All strings must come from localization files (ARB).
3. Use flutter_localizations and intl package.
4. Support two languages:
   - English (LTR)
   - Arabic (RTL)

5. RTL Support:
   - UI must adapt automatically for Arabic
   - Do not hardcode text direction
   - Use Directionality-aware widgets
   - Use start/end instead of left/right

6. Localization structure:
   - lib/l10n/app_en.arb
   - lib/l10n/app_ar.arb

7. UI Requirements:
   - Layout must work in both LTR and RTL
   - No broken alignment in Arabic
   - Text must fit in both languages

8. Language switching:
   - Allow switching between English and Arabic
   - Save user preference

9. Fonts:
   - Support Arabic fonts (e.g. Cairo, Noto Sans Arabic)
   - Use fallback fonts when needed

10. Testing:
   - Every screen must be tested in both languages
